he oil industry fostered colonial power and Baghdad's influence over Kirkuk, intercommunal violence and competing claims to the city's history took hold. The ethnicities of Kurds, Turkmens, and Arabs in Kirkuk were formed throughout a century of urban development, interactions between communities, and political mobilization. Ultimately, this book shows how contentious politics in disputed areas are not primordial traits of those regions, but are a modern phenomenon tightly bound to the society and economics of urban life.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Mai 2021) 0aEthnic conflictzIraqzKarkūkxHistoryy20th century. 0aEthnic conflictzIraqzKarkūkxHistoryy20th century. 0aEthnicityxPolitical aspectszIraqzKarkūkxHistoryy20th century. 0aEthnicityxPolitical aspectszIraqzKarkūkxHistoryy20th century. 0aPetroleum industry and tradezIraqzKarkūkxHistoryy20th century. 0aPetroleum industry and tradezIraqzKarkūkxHistoryy20th century. 7aHISTORY / Middle East / Iraq.2bisacsh  aIraq.  aKirkuk.  acolonialism.  adevelopment.  adisputed cities.  aethnic conflict.  aethnicity.  aoil.  apetroleum.  aurbanization.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020 Englishz978311070471608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020z9783110704518oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE History 2020 Englishz978311070473008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE History 2020z9783110704525oZDB-23-DEG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertSUP Complete eBook-Package 2019z978311069228040uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978150360914340uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781503609143423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9781503609143.jpg  a978-3-11-069228-0  SUP Comple